<p>Sweaty palms, a light headache, a faint feeling of hope. Those were all the feelings I experienced only a few days ago. I was waiting for my assignment marking. I had overworked and overstressed on finalizing every little detail and the result would finally be revealed. After repeatedly refreshing ladok - a swedish website for checking results - the mark appeared. For a short moment my headache increased and I started frantically clicking on my screen to refresh. But the letter didn‚Äôt change, it remained a big fat U. I had failed. And my heart sank. Within a moment I was in my bed, curled in a foetal position. Of course I called my boyfriend, fake crying on the phone. He came over immediately.</p>

<p>Now, he and I are different in various ways.</p>

<p>So after having brainstormed for a while, I did two things.</p>

